Agreement to Terms
Please read the following important terms and conditions before you download the Mazoin app. If you are the parent or legal guardian of a child under the age of 18 you are agreeing to these Terms on behalf of yourself and your children who are authorised to use the Mazoin App pursuant to these Terms. By downloading the Mazoin App you agree to these terms. If you do not agree to these terms, do not download the Mazoin App. 
We take our responsibilities as a provider of online and app-based games seriously and follow the Principles for online and app-based games (Principles) published by the Competition and Markets Authority (CMA). This means that, in particular, we will:
give you clear and accurate information on costs, the game and on us;
make it clear where there is an in-game promotion of paid-for content or promotion of any other product or service;
make sure that paid-for and non-paid-for options are presented clearly and given equal prominence;
not exploit or pressurise any game-players who are children to make a purchase or persuade others to make purchases for them; and
only take payments from you with your knowledge and express authorisation.
The information in this summary box summarises our main responsibilities under the Principles. It is not intended to replace the contract below which you should read carefully.
